Small level with intense fights, wether in interior between shelves, boxes and various warehouses elements, or long range passing through the main street, all type of players will find themselves in this new map making the link between our Warehouse project of 2014 and Seizure (2016) since the playable area is located directly between the grids of the two maps.

Excellent for bloody game types like Deathmatch or Gun-Games, but also warm-up due to its "competitive design like". Even Prop-Hunt players will enjoy playing on this level.

Hello, this is my first map, tell me if you like it! =D

![Introduction](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/17061503/gb/introduction.png "Introduction")

I noticed a distinct lack of dark DM based maps for CS:S (which nobody plays anymore, right?), so I set out and produced this, a long time ago, [6 months in fact.](http://gamebanana.com/wips/42554 "")

I may consider converting this to CS:Go should there be enough of an attraction, though I personally do not think it's up to the quality of which CS:Go demands, specifically, more detail to the exterior areas.

![Features](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/17061503/gb/features.png "Features")

- 3 level "Ware" / "Power" house, plus an accessible roof
- Dark low lighting levels throughout
- Good optimization for AI / offline play
- Balanced, various connectors / drop downs.

![Video](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/17061503/gb/video.png "Video")

This is it, ladies and gentlemen.
After many years of waiting, the day has finally come.

I present to you, the most balanced map in CS:S history.
Nevermore shall you hear complaints of a map being "too CT-sided" or "having too many hiding spots."

After many years of work and thousands of rounds of strenuous playtesting from millions of CS:S players worldwide including pro players like kennyS and pashabiceps, I was able to determine that this map is as balanced as a Counter-Strike map could ever get. There are no cheeky plant spots, headglitch spots, or any advantages for either team. This map is 100% balanced.

You're welcome, CS:S community.

Bowsy - [http://exgforums.com/](http://exgforums.com/ "EXG Forums")

Please if possible could I receive feedback for future updates to the map to really nail down on potentially issues with map and improve it.

Not only problems I am looking for but improvements too.

Please note this is the first alpha version and some changes have already been made, such as:

*Removed C4 spawn from CT spawn area.
*Removed Beauty Salon sign's from shop.

Place the .BSP into your Maps folder located in your CStrike folder. Do this whilst CSS is closed, if done whilst CSS is loaded - please make sure to restart CSS for the client to load the map properly into the maplist.

Directory:

D:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\common\Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps

I created this map back in 2012 and only shared it at a real Australian internet gaming cafe named Cyberhive (which the map is based on) - the cafe was really happy with the results but I've never shared it  publicly until now (life got in the way and I stopped playing CS:Source until now when I realized hey it wouldn't hurt to share this map I spent hundreds of hours on to the world!).

I've made four variants of this map in total, each of varying sizes and this is the SMALLEST variant of the map - it's very tight so there's plenty of quick, instant action to be had. Check out the largest variants of this map: cs_cyberhive_sundown and de_cyberhive_night
